name: ON SALE | Bad Boys "Back to Back" Crewneck | Black
description: Arguably the most underrated championship team in the modern era, the Detroit Pistons dominated the NBA of the Late 1980′s, winning Back-to-Back Titles over the Showtime Lakers in 1989 & the Blazers in 1990. Led by the great, Isiah Thomas, the Pistons embodied the blue collar work ethic of the Motor City and played the toughest brand of basketball the NBA would ever see, earning them the nickname, The Bad Boys! This goes out to Zeke, Coach Daly, Rodman, Mahorn, Laimbeer, Dumars, The Microwave, Salley and the rest of the “Bad Boys.” Draft Packs salutes the Back-to-Back NBA Champion, 1989-90 Detroit Pistons with this Limited Edition “Bad Boys” T-Shirt/Crewneck in OG Black & Pistons Blue ONLY AVAILABLE at www.DraftPacks.com LIMITED QUANTITY AVAILABLE! 50/50% Cotton Blend sweatshirt. Woven neck label. If you would like your crewneck more fitted, order one size down from your normal t-shirt size. Screen-printed Graphic on front.
